                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "Frozen plasma samples were thawed at room temperature and shaken before use. According to standard procedures [1], a total of 300 \u00b5l of a phosphate sodium buffer (70 mM Na2HPO4; 20 % (v/v) 2H2O; 0.025 % (v/v) NaN3; 0.8 % (w/v) sodium trimethylsilyl [2,2,3,3-2H4]propionate (TSP) pH 7.4) was added to 300 \u00b5l of each plasma sample, and the mixture was homogenized by vortexing for 30 s. A total of 450 \u00b5l of this mixture was transferred into a 4.25 mm NMR tube (Bruker BioSpin srl) for analysis.\n</p>\nRef:</br>\n[1] Bernini P, Bertini I, Luchinat C, Nincheri P, Staderini S, Turano P. Standard operating procedures for pre-analytical handling of blood and urine for metabolomic studies and biobanks. Journal of Biomolecular NMR. 2011;49:231\u2013243. doi: 10.1007/s10858-011-9489-1. PMID:21380509</br>",
