                        "description": "For each sample, monodimensional 1H NMR spectra were acquired using a standard Carr-Purcell-Meiboom-Gill (CPMG) [1] (cpmgpr1d.comp; Bruker BioSpin) pulse sequence, using 64 scans, 73,728 data points, a spectral width of 12,019 Hz and a relaxation delay of 4 s. This pulse sequence is designed for the selective observation of small molecule components in solutions containing macromolecules.\n</p>\nRef:</br>\n[1] Carr HY, Purcell EM. Effects of diffusion on free precession in nuclear magnetic resonance experiments. Physical Review. 1954;94:630\u2013638. doi: 10.1103/PhysRev.94.630.</br>",
